CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 5, 1963, pg. 3, reads: "Freedom Singers - Shown singing at the United Negro Protest Committee's meeting, Sunday, at Bethesda Presbyterian Church, Homewood, are the members of the Children's Choir of North View Heights Presbyterian Church, where Rev. John Garvin is minster. Mrs. Emma Davis is choir director. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Girls and boys in children's choir of North View Heights Presbyterian Church, performing in Bethesda Presbyterian Church for United Negro Protest Committee meeting
